message: "If you use this software or data, please cite it as below."
title: "Arabic Edu-ConvoKit: Adapting Educational Discourse Analysis to Arabic Classroom Conversations"
abstract: >-
  An open-source pipeline that adapts Edu-ConvoKit to Arabic mathematics
  classrooms, translating 11,839 NCTE elementary-mathematics utterances into
  Modern Standard Arabic with NLLB-200 and benchmarking five transformer
  encoders (AraBERT v2, MARBERT v2, mBERT, XLM-RoBERTa) plus TF-IDF baselines
  on three discourse tasks (focusing questions, student reasoning,
  conversational uptake) under both stratified and session-grouped 5-fold
  cross-validation. Includes forward-direction LaBSE translation-quality
  estimation, an MT-system-divergence robustness study (Helsinki MarianMT),
  a 199-term Arabic mathematical lexicon, and a zero-shot Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct
  LLM baseline.
